CAPE TOWN - Three men have been shot dead in Mitchells Plain. The shooting happened on Sunday night in Westridge. ALSO READ: WC has seen more than 400 mass shootings between June 2019 & December 2021 The police's Novela Potelwa said that the attack was believed to be gang-related. "Reports indicate that a gunman arrived at an address in Cheshire Street at about 9.30pm, asked for the owner by name, he then shot the owner and two others inside the house. All three died on the scene. The suspect is yet to be apprehended and investigations continue," she said.